Derby previously served as the director-general of the Public Enterprises Department and she'll be taking ove from acting CEO Mohammed Mahomedy. JOHANNESBURG - The Public Enterprises Department has announced the appointment of a new CEO Portia Derby. Derby was appointed earlier on Friday. Derby previously served as the director-general of the Public Enterprises Department and she'll be taking over from acting CEO Mohammed Mahomedy. Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan has thanked Mahomedy for his service at Transnet. 